775
01:18:22,410 --> 01:18:24,207
Don't sing.
She's scared enough.

776
01:18:24,370 --> 01:18:28,921
BEAVER: Shut up. There's, like, rat shit.
PETE: Hold on to my feet!

777
01:18:29,410 --> 01:18:31,207
HENRY:
Pete, do you see anything?

778
01:18:32,090 --> 01:18:37,084
PETE: Duds! We got her!
-Here's Josie.

779
01:18:44,570 --> 01:18:47,482
[HELICOPTER HOVERING]

780
01:19:09,050 --> 01:19:11,689
CURTIS: Blue Boy leader.
How we doing, bucko?

781
01:19:12,810 --> 01:19:17,884
-Right here, boss. Fast and hard.
-Wouldn't have it any other way.

782
01:19:19,490 --> 01:19:21,082
Sir?

783
01:19:23,330 --> 01:19:25,082
I see it.

784
01:19:37,210 --> 01:19:39,007
FEMALE: Don't hurt us.
MALE: We're dying.

785
01:19:39,170 --> 01:19:41,559
MALE: There is no infection here.
-Whose radio is that?

786
01:19:41,770 --> 01:19:44,568
It's not the radio.
They're putting it into our heads.

787
01:19:44,770 --> 01:19:46,840
FEMALE: We are helpless.
-There it is, gentlemen.

788
01:19:47,010 --> 01:19:50,207
MALE: There's no infection here.
-Directly into our heads.

789
01:19:50,530 --> 01:19:52,885
This gives you an idea
what we're up against.

790
01:19:54,810 --> 01:19:57,722
If anybody's thinking,
"Those poor, helpless little folk...

791
01:19:57,890 --> 01:20:01,849
...all naked and unarmed beside
their crashed intergalactic Winnebago...

792
01:20:02,010 --> 01:20:04,888
...what kind of a dog,
what kind of a monster...

793
01:20:05,050 --> 01:20:07,689
...could hear that heartbreak
and go in just the same?"

794
01:20:07,850 --> 01:20:12,765
-Well, I'm that dog. I'm that monster.
FEMALE: We are helpless. We are dying.

795
01:20:12,930 --> 01:20:15,649
CURTIS: These mothers are as harmless
as a fox in a henhouse.

796
01:20:15,810 --> 01:20:18,529
And I'm here to kick some ass!
Are you with me?

797
01:20:18,690 --> 01:20:20,442
-Yes, boss!
-Roger that, boss.

798
01:20:20,650 --> 01:20:21,765
Right on, boss.

799
01:20:22,810 --> 01:20:24,801
FEMALE:
Don't hurt us.

800
01:20:29,050 --> 01:20:30,768
I have a visual.

801
01:20:33,690 --> 01:20:35,362
Holy shit!

802
01:20:35,530 --> 01:20:37,407
Damn, look at the size of that.

803
01:20:38,810 --> 01:20:43,201
Blue Boy group, this is Blue Boy leader.
Target imminent. Go to level 4 readiness.

804
01:20:43,370 --> 01:20:45,440
Gentlemen, lock and load.

805
01:20:47,330 --> 01:20:48,604
Hellfires are hot.

806
01:20:50,210 --> 01:20:51,438
Sing it out, Owen!

807
01:20:51,930 --> 01:20:57,243
Blue Boy group, this is Blue Boy leader.
Clean up the forest, get rid of this trash!

808
01:20:57,410 --> 01:20:59,924
MALE: Don't hurt us.
FEMALE: Please, don't hurt us.

809
01:21:00,090 --> 01:21:03,002
MALE: There is no infection here.
FEMALE: We are helpless.

810
01:21:03,330 --> 01:21:05,685
-Fire at will!
CURTIS: Fire!

811
01:21:12,010 --> 01:21:13,159
[BEEPING]

812
01:21:37,610 --> 01:21:39,840
[GUNSHOTS]

813
01:22:15,970 --> 01:22:17,881
CURTIS:
Owen, get them out of there!

814
01:22:19,010 --> 01:22:20,284
It's gonna blow!

815
01:22:20,770 --> 01:22:24,285
Blue Boy group, withdraw at once.
I repeat, cease firing and back off!

816
01:22:24,450 --> 01:22:26,680
-We can get them!
OWEN: It's self-destructing.

817
01:22:27,090 --> 01:22:29,809
-Blue Boy group, get out of there!
-We're on top of it!

818
01:22:30,690 --> 01:22:32,487
CURTIS:
Owen, pull out now!

819
01:22:32,650 --> 01:22:35,847
OWEN: Pull out! Get out of there!
-Pull out!

820
01:23:01,530 --> 01:23:06,365
MOORE: Jonesy, I've been thinking
about our friend. Our Scooby-Doo buddy.

821
01:23:06,970 --> 01:23:10,519
For a long time I thought he was sent
to us to warn us about something.

822
01:23:10,810 --> 01:23:13,643
-I could never figure what it was.
JONES: Don't talk about him.

823
01:23:13,810 --> 01:23:17,883
MOORE: Not till today.
It was this, right now.

824
01:23:18,570 --> 01:23:23,644
-He wanted to warn us.
MR. GRAY: Tell me about your friend.

825
01:23:23,810 --> 01:23:28,600
-Did he show you that nifty trick?
MOORE: No. Jonesy's right.

826
01:23:29,010 --> 01:23:32,923
MR. GRAY: Come on, Pete. Let's talk.
-Bite my bag, motherfucker!

827
01:23:36,650 --> 01:23:41,724
All right, Pete, I'll bite.
Your bag and everything else.

828
01:23:45,490 --> 01:23:48,527
No, no! You bastard! No!

829
01:23:57,090 --> 01:23:58,967
Pete.

830
01:24:45,930 --> 01:24:48,160
Don't talk to him!
Get out of there!

831
01:24:50,050 --> 01:24:51,039
MR. GRAY:
Ah.

832
01:24:51,210 --> 01:24:52,199
[DOG GROWLS]

833
01:24:52,370 --> 01:24:54,838
-What's up?
-Thank God you came by, governor.

834
01:24:55,170 --> 01:24:57,638
I'm broke down here
and fearing for my life.

835
01:24:58,290 --> 01:24:59,848
That's a good-looking dog.

836
01:25:00,010 --> 01:25:02,001
-Where you headed?
-Gosselin's.

837
01:25:02,170 --> 01:25:04,638
Any chance you're going near there?

838
01:25:05,090 --> 01:25:06,762
That's where I'm going.

839
01:25:07,650 --> 01:25:11,165
Well, I believe your tailgate
has come open.

840
01:25:17,410 --> 01:25:19,048
Let's take a look.

841
01:25:26,410 --> 01:25:29,402
I see you have some cargo
you're taking to Blue Base.

842
01:25:35,250 --> 01:25:37,320
[SCREAMING]

843
01:25:40,890 --> 01:25:42,767
[DOG BARKS]

844
01:25:52,290 --> 01:25:54,565
MR. GRAY:
Got a treat for you, Ike.

845
01:25:57,410 --> 01:26:01,847
All you can eat.
Eat all the red stuff.

846
01:26:03,450 --> 01:26:08,922
Good doggy. Yes.
Good boy.

847
01:26:09,530 --> 01:26:13,603
Have your fill.
Tasty, tasty.

848
01:26:13,770 --> 01:26:15,044
Eat all you want--

849
01:26:15,210 --> 01:26:16,962
[SCREECHING]

850
01:26:18,610 --> 01:26:23,047
Jonesy.
What are you up to?

851
01:26:56,930 --> 01:26:58,249
Jonesy!

852
01:27:12,090 --> 01:27:13,648
[GROANS]

853
01:27:18,410 --> 01:27:20,082
Oh, God!

854
01:27:22,490 --> 01:27:24,606
[GROWLING]

855
01:27:39,610 --> 01:27:43,046
[ROARING]

856
01:27:58,850 --> 01:28:01,523
[GROANING]

857
01:28:10,290 --> 01:28:14,203
MAN: Halt or we'll fire!
You cannot leave the quarantine zone!

858
01:28:14,370 --> 01:28:16,440
-Halt!
-I think I just about halted here.

859
01:28:21,850 --> 01:28:23,329
CURTIS:
Come with me, Owen.

860
01:28:23,490 --> 01:28:26,368
I'll show you things
you'll wish you'd never seen.

861
01:28:27,290 --> 01:28:30,362
[WOMAN SOBBING]

862
01:28:30,530 --> 01:28:34,159
[BABY CRYING]

863
01:28:40,970 --> 01:28:43,609
MAN 1: How long we gotta be here?
CURTIS: It'll be all right.

864
01:28:47,970 --> 01:28:51,440
MAN 1: I demand to see my lawyer!
-There must be something they can do.

865
01:28:53,650 --> 01:28:55,163
MAN 2:
Don't worry, you'll be fine.

866
01:28:55,330 --> 01:28:57,560
MAN 1: When do we get out?
CURTIS: Within hours.

867
01:28:57,730 --> 01:29:01,769
-You can't do this to people in America!
MAN 2: I told you to stay over there!

868
01:29:01,930 --> 01:29:04,285
-My wife--
CURTIS: Government's doing what...

869
01:29:04,450 --> 01:29:07,362
...they can to get you out of here.
Don't worry. It's all right.

870
01:29:07,530 --> 01:29:09,998
We're doing everything
to make sure you're safe.

871
01:29:10,170 --> 01:29:12,923
We'll get you back to your homes
within hours.

872
01:29:22,130 --> 01:29:23,722
MAN:
All clear.

873
01:29:45,330 --> 01:29:47,969
Can I help you, sir?
What's your name?

874
01:29:48,130 --> 01:29:52,009
-Henry. Dr. Henry Devlin.
-A doctor? Good.

875
01:29:52,170 --> 01:29:53,762
We need doctors in there.

876
01:29:55,570 --> 01:29:58,004
Come on, laddie, I'll buy you a cup.

877
01:29:59,930 --> 01:30:04,367
-You, sir, where you from?
-Boston.

878
01:30:05,010 --> 01:30:10,368
Beantown? Great city.
We'll have you back there in no time.

879
01:30:10,530 --> 01:30:12,282
Maybe by morning.

880
01:30:13,330 --> 01:30:15,161
Hurry up, bucko.

881
01:30:25,210 --> 01:30:27,804
You see that crud on the faces
of children...

882
01:30:27,970 --> 01:30:31,963
...you know why I relish a turn
in the country like we had today.

883
01:30:32,890 --> 01:30:37,247
You were excellent out there, O.
It made me feel very proud to--

884
01:30:40,050 --> 01:30:43,725
Abe?
Abe, you okay?

885
01:30:45,090 --> 01:30:47,001
Abe?

886
01:30:49,490 --> 01:30:51,242
Yeah.

887
01:30:53,570 --> 01:30:58,690
Yeah, I'm fine. I'm fine.
I must be getting too old for this shit.

888
01:30:59,810 --> 01:31:02,483
I don't know what the hell
that was about.

889
01:31:15,850 --> 01:31:18,080
It's the only way, Owen.

890
01:31:18,850 --> 01:31:21,410
We've got to cauterize the site.

891
01:31:22,970 --> 01:31:24,881
They've all got to die.

892
01:31:26,210 --> 01:31:27,768
It's the only way.

893
01:31:27,970 --> 01:31:29,722
OWEN:
But we don't know that.

894
01:31:29,890 --> 01:31:34,168
Studies point to the strong possibility
of recovery for many exposed subjects.

895
01:31:34,330 --> 01:31:36,924
The studies show squat,
that's what they show.

896
01:31:37,090 --> 01:31:40,207
If Matheson had been in my spot
for the last quarter-century...

897
01:31:40,370 --> 01:31:42,838
...you'd have never made
it to your first jerk-off.

898
01:31:43,290 --> 01:31:47,488
Those gray bastards would have had you
for lunch back in Armpit, Kentucky.

899
01:31:47,650 --> 01:31:50,847
Some get better. At least
half will be over it in a few days--

900
01:31:51,010 --> 01:31:53,080
Which ones, Mother Teresa?

901
01:31:53,250 --> 01:31:57,368
Can you guarantee they won't take it
home like a present for the family?

902
01:31:57,570 --> 01:32:01,279
I'll tell you what you should be worried
about. What should be on your mind.

903
01:32:01,450 --> 01:32:03,008
Not these few unfortunates.

904
01:32:03,490 --> 01:32:05,924
What you should be worried
about is a hitchhiker.

905
01:32:06,090 --> 01:32:07,489
-What?
-A hitchhiker.

906
01:32:07,650 --> 01:32:10,642
Our greatest fear is that a grayboy
would catch a ride...

907
01:32:10,810 --> 01:32:14,644
...with somebody and would carry them
out of here, without being consumed.

908
01:32:14,890 --> 01:32:17,802
To scatter the infection,
like Johnny-fucking-Appleseed.

909
01:32:17,970 --> 01:32:20,120
-Are you sure there isn't such a person?
-No.

910
01:32:20,290 --> 01:32:22,758
But I am sure that if there is one
he won't get out.

911
01:32:22,930 --> 01:32:25,524
Not with the net my boys
put up around the Blue Zone.

912
01:32:25,770 --> 01:32:28,284
And if we do a thorough job
on the ones we've got.

913
01:32:28,450 --> 01:32:30,600
If we don't get gooey
about the little picture...

914
01:32:30,770 --> 01:32:32,840
...when our job is taking care
of the big one.

915
01:32:33,490 --> 01:32:34,764
Capisce?

916
01:32:35,170 --> 01:32:38,958
Owen, if you think this is easy for me,
you're crazier than my mother was.

917
01:32:40,450 --> 01:32:42,008
Those poor schmucks.

918
01:32:42,770 --> 01:32:46,365
They drive Chevrolets,
shop at Wal-Mart...

919
01:32:46,530 --> 01:32:48,441
...never miss an episode of Friends.

920
01:32:49,490 --> 01:32:51,287
These are Americans.

921
01:32:52,930 --> 01:32:55,046
The idea of slaughtering Americans...

922
01:32:57,730 --> 01:32:59,880
...it just turns my stomach.

923
01:33:03,770 --> 01:33:07,809
But I'll do it.
I'll do it because it needs to be done.

924
01:33:09,250 --> 01:33:13,528
So if we start at 2, we can be done
by 2:30. And it's all behind us.

925
01:33:14,410 --> 01:33:16,321
Except for the dreams.

926
01:33:19,170 --> 01:33:21,479
Yeah, except for them.

927
01:33:33,250 --> 01:33:36,481
What are you gonna tell Rita
about what you did here?

928
01:33:36,770 --> 01:33:40,206
What are you gonna tell Katrina
when she's old enough to ask?

929
01:33:43,730 --> 01:33:46,528
You know me, don't you?
I don't remember when we met...

930
01:33:46,690 --> 01:33:48,123
...but you know me.

931
